## Week 1, Day 3 — [date]
**Today:** Built structured output pipeline (Pydantic + Enum) over real log data; locked down both severity and category fields
**Learned:** Enum forces consistent values the model must follow; Pydantic validates data on the spot and fails loudly with clear errors if something doesn't match the schema — proved this myself with a standalone Person/age example before applying it to the real pipeline
**Stuck on:** Initially fuzzy on Pydantic/BaseModel — fixed by building a tiny non-LLM example from scratch first
**Tomorrow:** Day 4 — refine ingestion/classification pipeline, add basic error handling and retries# Daily Log

